reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Did the job
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this set for a recent one-week trip to London where I wanted to try carry-on only for the first time. I used a budget airline and the size of these bags were perfect for the overhead and under seat areas. The rolling was smooth and easy through parking lots, airports, subway stations, etc. They were roomy and I had plenty of space for what I brought with room left to bring home some souvenirs. I also love the color! Since it's only been one trip, I can't speak for durability or how the bag would do if it was checked, but they seem pretty sturdy. I'm looking forward to using these a lot in the future!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice travel set
reviews.reviewText: I just received my Bagsmart carryon and personal bag and am very pleased. Although, I haven’t used it yet, the spinner wheels seem awesome and it seems like a functional set for carryon travel. I like the lock feature and the ease of the personal bag fitting on the handle for easy rolling. It seems sturdy and durable, but it has not been put through real life testing yet. Very disappointed it doesn’t have a handle on the bottom for lifting the bag on to a luggage rack or putting in a trunk. This was a feature I used every time on my former carryon. It doesn’t seem as well made as my Samsonite, but it is much lighter weight when empty too. Great colors, ready to try it out!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Returned. Bagsmart carryon is couple inches shorter.
reviews.reviewText: Bagsmart carryon is couple inches shorter in length and height compared to Kenneth Cole reaction carryon in the picture. Kenneth Cole reaction is expensive to me over $200 only because you’re paying for the brand name but it does give you couple more inches and the build quality is beautiful in 2 tone colors with black & gold outline and the gold zippers are solid. So I decided to keep Kenneth Cole reaction but I haven’t finished packing yet with the shared carry on between myself and my husband for our future 3 weeks Philippines trip. It’s humid and hot over there all year long. But I’m still not completely confident yet if both brands can hold 3 weeks worth of clothes for international trips but I want to stack as much as I can and avoid checking in too many luggages as much as possible. I returned the bagsmart brand.
